The paper proposes a meta-learning approach for few-shot learning, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper discusses the use of entropy-based and inequality-minimization approaches to improve the generalizability of the meta-learner. These approaches are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and robotics (cs.RO). However, given that the paper focuses on few-shot learning, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning, we believe that cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV.
